<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7193> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7193" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Sulla with forces to aid Ascalis of Tingi in 81-80 and met his death (Plut. Sert 9.4-5). See Plut. Crass. 4.3, on Crassus' protector in southern Spain in 85, Vibius Paciacus or Pacciaecus: Munzer, noting the uncertainty in the tradition of the name, suggests that they may be the same. See RE, s. v. Paciaecus; MRR 2.313, on L. Vibius Paciaecus; Wiseman, NM 248, no. 300. See also A. J. N. Wilson, Emigration from Italy 30f.; B. Scardigli, Athenaeum 49, 1971, 244-250; P. 0. Spann, Sertorius 66-69, who thinks P. was sent by the governor of Hisp. Ult.; C. F. Konrad, Sertorius 37-38.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4219> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4219" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Sulla to aid King Ascalis of Mauretania against Sertorius, and died in battle against him (Plut. Sert. 9.2- 3; cf. Crass. 4.2)." .
